We are an organized guild, I was the guild leader of Mark of Draconians on M-T.  We have very few members at the moment BECAUSE we are NOT shouting for members.  We are inviting people who roleplay with us while we are in game and are not in a hurry as we are not in a hurry to powerlevel either or be the first guild camping every dungeon.  Our charter was already accepted weeks ago.  All we await is the head-count, but until we have those ten solid roleplayers, whether they enjoy grouping or playing a solo story, we will not shout for members just to get our guild name up next to our name.<br>
<br>
We do not care if your character is a soloist.  The guild will have guild-wars, but is not gathered together for the sake of war only.  What we care about is providing a story that is a jump off point for others to weave their own stories off of.<br>
<br>
Evermyst is our book, and each of it's member are it's chapters in the story.  We invite people to write their chapters.<br>
<br>
Hmm, does this make sense?   <p><img src="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg/evermyst/images/liuclose.gif" border="0">
