<br>
They have no idea or concept to their guild. No one can explain why their guild is called such and such. It's another blank empty name with no backgrounf, history, depth, or any storyline whatsoever. <br>
<br>
They should make people submit an in depth charter and make guild leaders accountable for the actions of their people. If they could arrange that it would take alot of the work off of CS reps in the end.<br>
<br>
Most of the guilds out there have zero idea what a guild is even meant to be. Seems most either think that a guild is meant to be a machine to uber out and make a server a hellhole for others, or that making a guild is an ego buffer.<br>
<br>
Being in leadership is a RESPONSIBILITY and once your there you have the affairs and well being of others to oversee. Many leaders I have met do not really care that much about the individuals to whom they are responsible to seeing that the needs of those they hold charge over are met. Being a leader oft means sacrificing self before others. <br>
<br>
Guilds were meant to be a fellowship, something with depth, rich in color...personally I despise the way guilds are done in EQ. They make it way too easy for any group of ubers to throw together a meaningless tag in an RPG and let too many people that don't even care about the conceptual nature of guilds as a general whole enter into fruition. It's a shame really when you think about it. <br>
<br>
VI talks about work so much, I think they should make guilds earn their guild tags <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
